76561197977314644,Recommended,330100,26204034,"Posted: 24 October, 2016",all,Puppet #7,"If you're into the ""Build a ship"" or ""Min-max"" style games, BossConstructor is one of those under the radar, hidden indie gems on steam.The game offers multiple seperate game modes, from quick skirmish matches to longer campaigns. It even has a seperate competitive mode using some specific predefinded missions- of which (<----This guy) currently sits on top of all of them ;P Come get me. (Currently under contest- nice Frice)Customizing your ship is done via an overhead, top down, 2d plane style set-up.Parts are added in line to one another, no overlapping/stacking like in Battleships forever, though there are parts which move that allow some more complicated builds for those interested in such.It has good selection of parts which unlock either via a discovery system or, a fast unlock-all option for looking to jump right in and get to building.Also, this game has one of the best Dev's a community could ever ask for- he's quick to reply on forums, fast to address bugs and puts an honest ear to feedback.Buy the game, if you dont like the genre: buy it anyway and gift it to a friend who does-"
