76561198067692156,Recommended,330100,15574081,"Posted: 26 April, 2015",all,yac,"Just very quickly for now:- great 2D space shooter with emphasis on building your own ship (boss) module by module- caring developer with lightning fast response (next day patch)- frequent patches bringing lots of new and improved stuffIn comparison with Reassembly:- grid based ship editor (simpler but less flexible)- battles occur on separate randomly generated maps (as opposed to Reassembly's huge continuous ecosystem)- ship size is currently rather limited, both by ship editor and by performance I reckon, but impressive beats of doom can be had- broken modules remain broken until the end of battle, forcing the player to adapt to new ship behavior and build their ship to survive these brutal scenarios - this rewards good engineering!I love it already and I have high hopes it's gonna get much better as it has potential to be as unique as Reassembly or SPAZ with its own mix of space shooting/engineering goodness."
